{"summary":"Create Employee Search LWC Component","plan":{"summary":"Implement an Employee Search Lightning Web Component (LWC) that allows Salesforce users to search Employee__c records by name. The solution consists of an Apex controller class (EmployeeSearchController) with a cacheable AuraEnabled method, and an LWC (employeeSearch) with a search input, search button, and lightning-datatable to display results. The existing Employee__c custom object with its fields (Employee_ID__c, Department__c, Email__c, Salary__c) will be used. The component will be configured to be available in Lightning App Builder.","riskLevel":"Low","steps":[{"num":1,"title":"Create Apex Class: EmployeeSearchController","type":"ApexClass","fullName":"EmployeeSearchController","detail":"Create the Apex class EmployeeSearchController with a single cacheable AuraEnabled static method searchEmployees(String searchText) that queries Employee__c records where Name contains the search text using SOQL LIKE operator. Includes proper error handling via AuraHandledException.","api":"Metadata API · ApexClass","action":"create","metadata":{"fullName":"EmployeeSearchController","body":"public with sharing class EmployeeSearchController {
    @AuraEnabled(cacheable=true)
    public static List<Employee__c> searchEmployees(String searchText) {
        if (String.isBlank(searchText)) {
            return new List<Employee__c>();
        }
        try {
            String searchKey = '%' + String.escapeSingleQuotes(searchText) + '%';
            return [
                SELECT Id, Name, Employee_ID__c, Department__c, Email__c, Salary__c
                FROM Employee__c
                WHERE Name LIKE :searchKey
                ORDER BY Name ASC
                LIMIT 200
            ];
        } catch (Exception e) {
            throw new AuraHandledException('Error retrieving employee records: ' + e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}"}},{"num":2,"title":"Create LWC HTML: employeeSearch","type":"ApexClass","fullName":"employeeSearch/employeeSearch.html","detail":"Create the HTML template for the employeeSearch LWC. Includes a lightning-card container, a search input field (lightning-input), a Search button (lightning-button), a lightning-datatable to display matching Employee__c records with columns for Employee Name, Employee ID, Department, and Email, and a conditional message displayed when no records are found.","api":"Metadata API · LightningComponentBundle","action":"create","metadata":{"fullName":"employeeSearch","type":"LWC_HTML","body":"<template>
